FT  10 SEP 93 / S Africa death toll rises to 32
Gunmen struck yesterday in South Africa's troubled black townships, raising
the death toll in political violence to at least 32 people in 24 hours,
Reuter reports from Johannesburg. Police reported seven deaths during
scattered attacks in Natal province while, at Katlehong township east of
Johannesburg, two blacks died in an ambush on their car.
President FW de Klerk said supporters of the African National Congress and
its rival Inkatha Freedom Party could be involved in the latest violence. to
